str2: For. A primary particle; properly, assigning a reason.

str2: I am, exist. The first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist.

parse: Verb - Perfect Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Plural
str2: From pro and horao; to behold in advance, i.e. to notice previously, or to keep in view.
Trophimus, a Christian of Ephesus in Asia. From trophe; nutritive; Trophimus, a Christian.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Ephesian, of Ephesus. From Ephesos; an Ephesian or inhabitant of Ephesus.
With. A primary preposition denoting union; with or together.

str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
In, on, among. A primary preposition denoting position, and instrumentality, i.e. A relation of rest; 'in, ' at, on, by, etc.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
A city, the inhabitants of a city. Probably from the same as polemos, or perhaps from polus; a town.

parse: Verb - Imperfect Indicative Active - 3rd Person Plural
str2: From nomos; properly, to do by law, i.e. To accustom; by extension, to deem or regard.
Neuter of hostis as conjunction; demonstrative, that; causative, because.
Paul, Paulus. Of Latin origin; Paulus, the name of a Roman and of an apostle.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To lead in, bring in, introduce. From eis and ago; to introduce.

str2: A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.

Neuter of hieros; a sacred place, i.e. The entire precincts of the Temple.
